column4: Experience Using Digital Tools in Learning
column6: I understand the concept and importance of digital transformation in language learning.
column7: I recognize that digital transformation brings many benefits to learners.
column8: I find it very easy to implement digital transformation in my major's learning.
column9: The school has clear policies to encourage and promote students in implementing digital transformation in learning.
column10: The school provides sufficient materials and training programs related to digital transformation.
column11: I have opportunities to participate in courses or workshops on implementing digital transformation in learning organized by the school.
column12: My lecturers integrate knowledge about digital transformation into their lectures.
column13: Lecturers and peers encourage me to apply technology in learning activities.
column14: I have sufficient devices (computer, Internet, etc.) and tools to apply digital technology in learning and work.
column15: I have access to online learning platforms and tools (LMS, MOOCs, etc.)
column16: I can proficiently use digital tools for learning in my major.
column17: I can easily access digital tools that support my learning.
column18: I am willing to regularly use technology in learning to adapt to digital transformation.
column19: I regularly update myself on trends in digital transformation in my major.
column20: I am willing to learn additional digital skills to improve the quality of my learning.
column21: I support the implementation of digital transformation in teaching and learning language majors.
column22: I am willing to introduce digital tools used in learning to other students.
column23: I am willing to share my digital skills with other students.
